Section 1:
SLS 251ES-4 ORIGINAL
2025 First Extraordinary Session
BY SENATOR KLEINPETER AND REPRESENTATIVE BEAULLIEU
ELECTION DAYS. Changes election dates for the spring 2026 statewide election for
submission of proposed constitutional amendments. (Item #1) (gov sig)
1 AN ACT
2 To amend and reenact Section 2 of Act No. 218 of the 2025 Regular Session of the
3 Legislature, Section 2 of Act No. 219 of the 2025 Regular Session of the Legislature,
4 Section 3 of Act No. 221 of the 2025 Regular Session of the Legislature, Section 8
5 of Act No. 222 of the 2025 Regular Session of the Legislature, and Section 2 of Act
6 No. 223 of the 2025 Regular Session of the Legislature and to repeal Act No. 212 of
7 the 2025 Regular Session of the Legislature, relative to designating the statewide
8 election for submitting proposed constitutional amendments contained in joint
9 resolutions concurred in during the 2025 Regular Session of the Legislature to the
10 electors of the state; to provide for a special statewide election to be held on May 16,
11 2026, for the purpose of submitting proposed constitutional amendments to the
12 electors of the state; to provide for the conduct of such election; to change the date
13 on which the proposed constitutional amendments shall be submitted to the electors;
14 to provide for effectiveness; and to provide for related matters.
15 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
16 Section 1. A special statewide election shall be held on Saturday, May 16, 2026, for
17 the purpose of submitting to the electors of the state proposed constitutional amendments
