SLS 251ES-4 ORIGINAL
SB NO. 2
1 is hereby amended and reenacted to read as follows:
2 Section 2. Be it further resolved that this proposed amendment shall be
3 submitted to the electors of the state of Louisiana at a statewide election to be held
4 on April 18, 2026, if House Bill No. 625 of the 2025 Regular Session of the
5 Legislature of Louisiana becomes effective. If House Bill No. 625 of the 2025
6 Regular Session of the Legislature of Louisiana does not become effective, this
7 proposed amendment shall be submitted to the electors of the state of Louisiana at
8 a statewide election to be held on November 3, 2026. May 16, 2026.
9 Section 8. Act No. 212 of the 2025 Regular Session of the Legislature is hereby
10 repealed in its entirety.
11 Section 9. This Act shall become effective upon signature by the governor or, if not
12 signed by the governor, upon expiration of the time for bills to become law without signature
13 by the governor, as provided by Article III, Section 18 of the Constitution of Louisiana. If
14 vetoed by the governor and subsequently approved by the legislature, this Act shall become
15 effective on the day following such approval.
The original instrument and the following digest, which constitutes no part
of the legislative instrument, were prepared by Senate Legislative Services.
The keyword, summary, and digest do not constitute part of the law or proof
or indicia of legislative intent. [R.S. 1:13(B) and 24:177(E)]
DIGEST
SB 2 Original 2025 First Extraordinary Session Kleinpeter
Proposed law repeals provisions designating April 18, 2026, as a date for a special statewide
election.
Present law provides for submission to the voters of certain constitutional amendments on
the following dates:
Act 218 relative to the proposed St. George community school system - April 18,

Section 2:
2026.
Act 219 relative to mandatory retirement of judges - April 18, 2026.
Act 221 relative to authority for parishes to exempt business inventory from ad
valorem taxes and to reduce percentage of fair market value applicable to
business inventory - April 18, 2026.
Act 222 relative to application of state monies to the unfunded accrued liability of
the Teachers' Retirement System of Louisiana - April 18, 2026.
Act 223 relative to authorizing additional positions in the unclassified state civil
service and prohibit their removal except by law - April 18, 2026.
Proposed law changes the date for submission to the voters of the constitutional amendments
from April 18, 2026, to May 16, 2026.
