SB 2 Original 2025 First Extraordinary Session Kleinpeter
Proposed law repeals provisions designating April 18, 2026, as a date for a special statewide
election.
Present law provides for submission to the voters of certain constitutional amendments on
the following dates:
Act 218 relative to the proposed St. George community school system - April 18,
2026.
Act 219 relative to mandatory retirement of judges - April 18, 2026.
Act 221 relative to authority for parishes to exempt business inventory from ad
valorem taxes and to reduce percentage of fair market value applicable to
business inventory - April 18, 2026.
Act 222 relative to application of state monies to the unfunded accrued liability of
the Teachers' Retirement System of Louisiana - April 18, 2026.
Act 223 relative to authorizing additional positions in the unclassified state civil
service and prohibit their removal except by law - April 18, 2026.
Proposed law changes the date for submission to the voters of the constitutional amendments
from April 18, 2026, to May 16, 2026.
